Is it possible to prevent an NSURLRequest from caching data or remove cached data following a request?

Usually it's easier to create the request like this NSURLRequest *request = [NSURLRequest requestWithURL:url cachePolicy:NSURLRequestReloadIgnoringCacheData (1 more line was trimmed) Then create the connection NSURLConnection *conn = [NSURLConnection connectionWithRequest:request delegate:self]; and implement the connection:willCacheResponse: method on the delegate. Just returning nil should do it. - (NSCachedURLResponse *)connection:(NSURLConnection *)connection willCacheResponse:(NSCachedURLResponse *)cachedResponse { return nil; (1 more line was trimmed)
